TASK_DESCRIPTION=The intent fallback (shell/intent-fallback.sh + shell/doey-intent-dispatch.sh) currently uses Haiku but feels slow. Investigate: (1) what model is actually being called, (2) can we use a faster model (claude-haiku-4-5, or fastest available), (3) reduce prompt size, (4) stream response, (5) cut cold-start overhead. User suggested 'opus instant' — likely meant fastest/lowest-latency model available. Goal: sub-second response for typical unknown-command corrections. See docs/intent-fallback.md.
